PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783961289
OL,3,CCampaigner 'over the moon' as
OL,4,CHillsborough Law returns to Commons
OL,6,F"People have to tell the truth,
OL,7,Fwhoever they are. The lies have cost
OL,8,Fmillions. The cover-ups have cost
OL,9,Fmillions. The truth costs nothing."
OL,11,FAfter the disaster, key public
OL,12,Fservants, including the police, were
OL,13,Ffound to have not told the truth about
OL,14,Fthe decisions taken leading up to the
OL,15,Ffatal crush at the Leppings Lane end
OL,16,Fof the ground.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783961289
OL,3,CCampaigner 'over the moon' as
OL,4,CHillsborough Law returns to Commons
OL,6,FBoth Sir Keir and his likely
OL,7,Fsuccessor, Andy Burnham have expressed
OL,8,Fsupport for the law change, but it has
OL,9,Fbeen repeatedly delayed over concerns
OL,10,Ffrom the security services about how
OL,11,Fit could impact spies.
OL,13,FThe Government now believes it has
OL,14,Freached a point where individual
OL,15,Femployees and ex-employees of the
OL,16,Fintelligence services will be covered
OL,17,Fby a duty of candour, without
OL,18,Fcompromising national security.
OL,20,FThis will be set out in amendments to
OL,21,Fthe Bill, due to be debated this week.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
